column2: 12 writers all DMing a narrative element of the story in each server
to be great at something you have to be willing to admit you have the capacity to be great
if you have no secrets are you ever truly free? if not even your name is your own do you have any power?

column5: You can control winds and the weather.
You strive to keep up with and outpace the competition.
You can restructure the physical and metaphysical.
You have powers over urban environments and denizens.
You control ice, snow, and freezing temperatures.
You have divine abilities related to crafting and art.
You operate in the darkness and take away the light.
You have the power to end lives and destroy undead.
You have the power to spoil and deteriorate matter.
You can bring about hallucinations and restlessness.
You are a conduit for divine devastation.
You have the power to enter and manipulate dreams.
You have the power to dry and crumble what opposes you.
You see and understand hidden inevitabilities.
You liberate yourself and others from shackles and constraints.
You control electricity, thunder, and storms.
You’re unnaturally lucky and keep out of harm’s way.
Your physical power is bolstered by divine strength.
You command powers associated with the moon.
You hold power over animals and plants.
You fill minds with horror and dread.
You punish those who displease you with the sharp sting of pain.
You evoke passion, whether as love or lust.
You strive to perfect your mind, body, and spirit.
You protect secrets and keep them hidden.
You have a painful connection to melancholy and sadness.
You wield power over the spiritual.
You command the power of the stars.
You harness the power of the sun and other light sources, and punish undead.
You reign over the flow of time.
You deceive others and cause mischief.
You pierce lies and discover the truth.
You wield power to rule and enslave others.
Your magic carries close ties to the undead.
You control water and bodies of water.
You hold power over wealth, trade, and treasure.

column13: Advantage on Saving Throws against Control Effects. Can't be Slowed

column7: Was sworn to Protect Vai, when she died he had no purpose and sought to find himself in the Mountains to the West.
Was Shen'Ra's Consort who heeded his words to help the Elves and felt remorse for forsook her duty
The Keeper of Knowledge, Records, and Law.
The Stone Father, King, and Judge. The one that knows the weight of rule, and upholds the law.
The Watcher of the Mountains, the stoic, still, and resolved one that warms of danger and conceals home from your enemies.
Mother Spring, who's gives life, grows food, raises young, and keeps the Father's judgment honest.
The fickle and enigmatic spirit of Creativity. Who spurs Builders and Artisans into making their great works.
The forge that burns, the artist of war, the fire of hate.
The wealthy and the poor, the one who knows the risk and who urges decisiveness.
The Defender of home, the Destroyer of enemies, and the pride of the Father.
The transiet spirit of the Dwarves, who always finds where they were meant to be.
The creater of home, builder of cities and roads. Often considered to be a Druid
The peerless craftsman, he creates finery and technology, the true follower of the Muse.
The maiden whom you fight for, who pours your ale and warms your bed. You must protect her and provide for her or you have no worth. The Pride of the Mother.
